# Ranse build-time secrets.
#
# These keys are prompted during the Deploy-to-Cloudflare flow and pushed
# as Worker Secrets. Runtime config (APP_URL, ADMIN_EMAIL, SUPPORT_DOMAIN,
# LLM_DEFAULT_MODEL) lives in wrangler.jsonc `vars`, NOT here.
#
# Leave both values BLANK. `bun run deploy` auto-generates strong random
# values; any weak prefill (e.g. "change-me...") is regenerated.
#
# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# Session signing + single-use admin bootstrap.
COOKIE_SIGNING_KEY=
ADMIN_BOOTSTRAP_TOKEN=

# ────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
# NOT prompted during deploy:
#   • Provider API keys (OPENAI_API_KEY, ANTHROPIC_API_KEY, etc.) — add
#     them in-app at Settings → LLM providers, or `wrangler secret put`
#     post-deploy if you prefer Worker-wide scope. Workers AI is the
#     default and requires no keys.
#   • CLOUDFLARE_AI_GATEWAY_TOKEN — only needed if you manually enable
#     gateway authentication.
